sentences: In 1985, he graduated with a double major in television-radio-film and marketing management from Syracuse University's S. I. Newhouse School of Public Communications.
In 2002, Robinson was appointed the head of TV at Adam Sandler's Happy Madison Productions.
In 2017, Robinson signed a four-year agreement with Sony Pictures Television that will have him launch his own production company, Doug Robinson Productions (DRP).
In September 2017, DRP sold its first family comedy series to ABC.
